  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You implant a powerful aversion in the subject's brain, the effects of which depend on the aversion.<br><br>- Creature or Object: The subject prefers not to be within 30 ft of the creature or object, and will actively try to move away it it comes too close.<br>- Word or Phrase: The subject avoids speaking the word or phrase.<br>- Action: The subject will not perform the action.<br>- Event: The subject will not take part in or attend the event, if possible.<br><br>The subject tries its best to follow this behavior, but will not put itself in danger to do so. If forced to take an action involving the thing it is averse to, it takes a -2 penalty to attack rolls, ability checks and skill checks for that action. The aversion counts as a weak source of fear for the purpose of the Magen: Narakumi no Jutsu technique (p136). This technique can be dispelled.</p>\n\n\n\n",
